node.text:
Riley and I have always made our best efforts to be self-aware, and to reflect on where we stand as ‘influencers’ on these social media platforms, and on this planet. The mark we leave in the mind’s of our viewers, and on the environment is important to us! I think 2020 has made us realise what’s really important, more than ever.. 

So, what do you guys want to see more of, or less of? Now’s your chance ⛵️🐚🎣🔧👨🏻‍🔬🔮🎸🤿🧘 let us know in the comments. And don’t forget to join us in our latest video on YT. x

Track by @pat.devlin_

node.text:
If you missed our latest video, we share some pretty damn exciting news with you guys.  We are overwhelmed with gratitude that two of our favourite marine companies want to be a part of our project 🥳

Essentially the way we are going to move around the world, with sails and electric propulsion, has been taken care of. This is HUGE. We are one step closer to pulling this off. In fact, maybe two or three steps closer 🥺💙🌎 

@doyle_sails , the most reputable sail makers in the world. Riley has been banging on about these guys for over a year now and he’s obsessed with their cableless sails. 😎😎😎

And @oceanvolt , the leaders in the electric propulsion and regeneration industry. We’re so excited to see what the future looks like for them. 😻

We have each and every one of YOU guys to thank for this. We couldn’t have got here without your support, your comments, emails of advice, years and years of watching our videos and sharing them with your friends. Don’t know what else to say other than we feel like the luckiest people on earth!! It looks like we might just get to build our new dream home on the ocean.. 👨‍👩‍👦⛵️✨ #sailinglavagabonde #doylesails #oceanvolt

Track by @luistrindademusic my golly what a voice! ⁣
⁣

node.text: This will be the third week we’ve had away from posting videos (sorry, there won’t be another video tomorrow!). As scary as it has been taking a step back, it’s also been a huge relief. A reminder to myself that WE make the rules, and a silly algorithm doesn’t own us hahaha. We’ve been doing what’s best for our family lately 🧡 still creating content up in north west of Australia (which we cannot wait to share with you… 🐋🚤🦀🌞🏖⛺️) hanging out with friends, completing a running challenge and locking in travel plans for our next big adventure, leaving Australia 29/09 !! Thank YOU, for being here for it all.

node.text:
Todays thoughts.. hopping on a sailboat and setting off into the horizon with a guy I’d only known for a month was a tad outrageous 🤣⚡️🌊🌚⛵️🌴👣. What was only supposed to be a ‘summer romance’ spent island hopping the Greek Islands with Riley, turned into thousands of nautical miles, a lotta countries (I’ve lost count now), a YouTube channel, a couple of kids, new boats and the most incredible experiences of my life. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Are you one of those people who has to say yes to every opportunity that comes your way even though some are just plain nuts? 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#soznotsozmum #sailinglavagabonde

node.text:
Wildflower season here in West Oz 🌸 only a month left until our next epic adventure abroad.. ✈️✈️✈️ I have mixed feelings about saying goodbye to Australia this time around, with all that’s going on in the world. But the ocean is home and we’ve got big fish to fry..🕺🏼⛵️☄️🤠 
*Also super rando but I was thinking of auctioning off my old brown ratty hat to raise some money for a good cause. (Swipe to see my hat lol). She’s 8 years old, has sailed somewhere around 70,000 nautical miles, visited 40+ countries and lives to tell the tale. Who’d bid on her? 🤣🤣🤣

node.text:
Hey crew,
As a lot of you might already know, with the arrival of Darwin we have come to find it quite difficult to post each week. We didn’t think we needed time off for ‘maternity leave’ but two months after Darwin has joined us, we think we might need to take that time to just chill. This is the first time we haven’t put up a video in 4 years! It has actually caused us a lot of heartache and anxiety here at La Vaga HQ. Many of you will say that it is fine and to make sure we are looking after ourselves but when you work so hard at something it is extremely difficult to take a step back, not knowing what may happen. Anyway, despite the unknown ambiguities of the almighty YT algorithm and what it could ultimately mean to have one or two weeks without posting a video, this is what we have to do as a family at the moment. We’re currently camping, diving and we intend to spend some time offline ❤️. Thanks for being here and for your support. We hope to see you all in a couple of weeks. 

Love from the crew from La Vagabonde,
Elayna, Riley, Lenny and Darwin.

node.text: Darwin. All smiles. Makes the sweetest “gaaaahhhh” sounds and just wants to chat all the time. He wants to be on someone during the day ALL DAY so my back is pretty well cactus, but he sleeps straight through the night, to the point where I actually have to wake him to feed him. He slid into our family and lifestyle so easily, the perfect little addition ❤️ (although he’ll be the reason we’ll have to miss our first Monday ep in 4 years… but whatever, he’s a cutie and all is forgiven hahaha)
